Diff between update() vs updateMany() ?

update() works bit similar to updateMany()

if we are using updateOne() and updateMany() method and not using $set operator while updating it gives error.

Below query is not updating by $set hence it will replace the full docs with new one _id remains same.
db.products.update({_id :ObjectId("4erfgy65esdr654esdxdse")},{email:"vijay.vaidya@accionlabs.com"})

//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


db.hobbies.insertMany([{_id:"yoga", name:""Yoga"},{_id:"cooking", name:"Cooking},{_id:"hiking",name:"Hikinh"}]
, {ordered : false})

By default, when using insertMany(), inserts are ordered - that means, that are inserting process stops
if any error occurs.

You can change this by switching to "unordered inserts" - your inserting process will then continue, even if 
errors occured.

In both the cases, no successful inserts (before the error) will be rolled back.

by defauly insertMany works as a {ordered:true}, but if we want to execute in unorder way so that if query gets fails
due to duplicate id still rest of the documents should get insert. 
for which we can use { ordered: fasle}.


